   <h2><center>Getting OneTime</center></h2>
</div>

<p>Various ways to get OneTime:</p>

<ul>

<li><p>Download the full package as a .tar.gz file: <a href="onetime-ONETIMEVERSION.tar.gz"
    >onetime-ONETIMEVERSION.tar.gz</a>.<br/>
    (This is the recommended way for non-Windows.)</p></li>

<li><p>Download the full package as a zip file: <a href="onetime-ONETIMEVERSION.zip"
    >onetime-ONETIMEVERSION.zip</a>.<br/>
    (This is the recommended way for Windows.)</p></li>

<li><p>You could just download the <a href="onetime" >standalone
    script</a> directly, if you don't want the README, the test suite,
    or other incidental files.</p></li>

<li><p>OneTime is packaged in <a href="http://debian.org/">Debian
    GNU/Linux</a> now.  If you run the "testing" distribution of
    Debian or higher, do
    <tt>'sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;update&nbsp;&amp;&amp;&nbsp;sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;install&nbsp;onetime'</tt>
    (or the equivalent in your preferred package management
    interface).</p>
    <p><em>Note that as of 24 July 2013, the version of OneTime packaged
    in Debian may be a major version number behind this upstream
    release.  We'll try to get Debian updated as soon as
    possible.</em></p></li>

</ul>

